ent under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nWe need to weigh strengths vs weaknesses. For long-distance flights, reliability, decision-making, stress handling, teamwork, communication, technical competence (weather, navigation, computer), ability to anticipate danger, spatial vision, concentration, problem solving are important. Also professional development (willingness to learn) matters.\n\nCandidate A: strong anticipation, complex connections, spatial vision, leadership. Weakness: unfriendly (could affect crew cooperation), unhealthy eating (potential health risk for long flights). No info on stress handling, decision speed, communication. Leadership good but unfriendly may hinder teamwork. Unhealthy diet could affect stamina.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious, handles stress well, good weather assessment, computer skills. Weakness: pretentious, wrong tone. Communication tone could affect crew. No info on decision speed, anticipation, spatial vision. But stress handling and weather assessment are crucial.\n\nCandidate C: quick correct decisions, concern for others, excellent attention, but communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education. Egocentric and communication issues could harm teamwork. Lack of willingness to develop may be issue for long-term suitability.\n\nCandidate D: responds adequately to unexpected events, concentration, problem solving, responsibility. Weakness: moody, loner. Moodiness could affect crew morale; loner may affect teamwork. No info on stress handling, weather assessment, anticipation.\n\nWe need to pick provisional favorite. Which candidate balances strengths and weaknesses best? Candidate B seems strong on stress handling, conscientiousness, weather, computer skills, which are technical and stress criteria. Weaknesses are pretentiousness and tone, which affect communication but maybe manageable. Candidate A has strong anticipation and spatial vision, but unfriendly and health concerns. Candidate D has strong problem solving and responsibility but moodiness and loner. Candidate C has quick decisions and attention but communication and egocentric.\n\nProbably Candidate B is best provisional.\n\nWe need to note uncertainties: lack of info on decision speed for B, anticipation, spatial vision, teamwork beyond tone, etc. Also missing info from other agents about other candidates.\n\nWhat would change vote? If other agents reveal that another candidate has strong teamwork and no communication issues, or that B has serious egocentric traits, etc.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing.\n\nMETADATA_JSON with vote \"Candidate B\"."}
